[00:09.58]Born in the hush of a brand-new year
[00:13.01]Y2K skies, the future unclear
[00:16.44]Tiny hands wrapped around my thumb
[00:19.87]Didn’t know yet what you’d become
[00:23.29]Sleepless nights, late-night drives
[00:26.72]Learning your laugh, learning your cries
[00:30.15]Time felt slow, then it learned to run
[00:33.58]I held the world in you my little son
[00:37.01]They say time flies when love is strong
[00:40.43]I blinked once and you were gone
[00:43.86]You were a child, you’re a son
[00:47.29]Still my reason when days feel long
[00:50.72]From scraped-up hands to finding your song
[00:54.15]I’ve been watching you all along
[00:57.57]Every step, every wrong and right
[01:01.00]You grew your wings right in my sight
[01:04.43]I’m proud of who you’ve become
[01:07.86]I see a big heart in you my son
[01:11.29]Bob the Builder fixing dreams
[01:14.71]Danny Phantom in between
[01:18.14]Fairly Odd wishes late at night
[01:21.57]Jimmy Neutron thinking bright
[01:25.00]Avatar teaching balance and fire
[01:28.43]Hannah Montana—your first stage desire
[01:31.85]With a mop for hair, a mic in your hand
[01:35.28]Singing “a moment like this”, you took your stand
[01:38.71]Drake and Josh, iCarly laughs
[01:42.14]Sweet Life chaos, Wizards’ magic crafts
[01:45.56]Charmed spells played with your cousin near
[01:48.99]You made the ordinary disappear
[01:52.42]I saw the spark before you did
[01:55.85]A quiet fire no one hid
[01:59.28]You were a child, you’re a son
[02:02.70]Learning who you’d grow into
[02:06.13]Every note, every truth you sung
[02:09.56]You were already becoming you
[02:12.99]Through TV glow and living room lights
[02:16.42]You practiced dreams on borrowed time
[02:19.84]I’m proud of who you’ve become
[02:23.27]I still see that child in you my son
[02:26.70]Saxophone case, marching lines
[02:30.13]Counting steps, keeping time
[02:33.56]Jazz band nights, campus days
[02:36.98]Music pulling you your own way
[02:40.41]Piano keys under thoughtful hands
[02:43.84]Smart enough to question the plan
[02:47.27]U.C.A. halls, you earned your place
[02:50.70]Purpose written on your face
[02:54.12]I worried, I hoped, I let you go
[02:57.55]Held my breath, then watched you grow
[03:00.98]You don’t need me like you did before
[03:04.41]But even now I love you more and more
[03:07.84]You were a child, you’re my son
[03:11.26]Still my pride when the lights go dim
[03:14.69]Every mile that you’ve outrun
[03:18.12]I see a strength rising in you
[03:21.55]You made your way, you found your voice
[03:24.98]You turned your fear into a choice
[03:28.40]I’m proud who you’ve become
[03:31.83]Forever a child, forever a son
[03:35.26]From year two-thousand to here and now
[03:38.69]I’d choose you again, I’d show you how
[03:42.12]No matter how far, no matter where you run
[03:45.54]I’m always a parent and you a son
